For many years, AC/DC have been considered the thinking man's rock band. The popularity of the band has led to a number of biographies over the years, some good, many bearely readable. But this encyclopaedia is something different: taking key elements and subjects surrounding DC - songs, albums, personnel, gigs, events and numerous other subjects - and presenting them in alphabetical order, with each entry illustrated accordingly. The authors get to the heart of the matter in hundreds of individula ways.
